      "description": "Solid budget-friendly project or daily with a strong-running drivetrain and good mechanical bones. Engine pulls well, transmission shifts through the range, and the car has the kind of honest wear you\u2019d expect from something that\u2019s been driven instead of parked. A great candidate for someone who appreciates a usable platform with plenty of life left and room to sort cosmetics to their taste. If you want an inexpensive car with capable road manners and dependable core hardware, this one is worth a look.",
